00:02:21.770 --> 00:02:29.040
He takes those descriptions and prints them
beneath 19th century images of slaves. He

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:40.940
called it "Runaways." The series was made
up of ten prints. Now part of the point in

00:02:40.940 --> 00:02:45.200
doing this is to try to get at the ways that
slavery and the language around it continues

00:02:45.200 --> 00:02:54.340
to be important to us today. They read and
looked very similar to the real thing. We

00:02:54.340 --> 00:03:00.180
always imagine that slavery is something in
the past and that we as a society have gotten

00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:06.860
over it. It's sort of gone. But we still feel
its effects. A reminder that his identity

00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:16.590
